where formula_16 is the electric scalar potential along the centerline between points 1 and 2.

Thus, we can associate an effective &quot;voltage drop&quot; formula_37 with an inductor (even though our basic understanding of induced emf is based on the vector potential rather than the scalar potential), and consider it as a load element in Kirchhoff&#x27;s voltage law,

